{"key":"processedPost-6146503","value":{"id":6146503,"first":6141570,"last":6147153,"when":1160333751,"utime":"10/08/06 09:55 PM","content":"Properly prepared grains will appear dry in the jar.  I always make mine on the dry side because I only use the grains as spawn to bulk substrates.  Grains prepared a bit dry will colonize much faster than if they're too wet.  I use the rule of thumb that the grains should be twice their original dry size, but no larger.<br />RR","title":"Re: Here's one for you expert growers!","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}